          Hello Joy1010,
          The infinitive is the base form of the verb. It is sometimes use with 'to' before it and sometimes without 'to'. The infinitive is highlighted in these examples:
            I want to be a doctor.
            She helped me find my bag.
            You should go home.
            He doens't know know what to do.
          You can read more about the infinitive here:
          https://learnenglish.britishcouncil.org/grammar/english-grammar-reference/infinitives
          https://learnenglish.britishcouncil.org/grammar/english-grammar-reference/verbs-followed-infinitive
          https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infinitive
          Peter
          The LearnEnglish Team
